metadata.name: Euphonic #752
metadata.description:
Euphonic is an exploration of the emergent visual properties that arise from placing layers of simple lines atop one another.

In general this effect is called the Moir√© effect. This effect really feels best in the tactile - when you have a printed page and an acetate sheet. This piece attempts to recreate that tactile joy.

This is built in WebGL 2 and so doesn't work in Safari 14 and below. All latest browsers will work as expected.

metadata.name: impossible cathedrals #23
metadata.description:
When the Impressionists first exhibited their work, they derided as lunatics by the art establishment. The vitriol then -- "wallpaper in its embryonic state is more finished than that seascape" (referring to Impression: sunrise by Monet) -- reminds me of criticism that generative art, and the NFT world more generally, are subject to now. "Impossible cathedrals" is a tribute to rebels who dare to see the world differently. 

Since generative art is often criticized as cold and austere, I took this as a challenge to reproduce the spirit of impressionism. Impossible cathedrals -- interwoven arches that cannot exist in reality -- hint at some of the favorite subjects of the impressionists.

The title alludes to Italo Calvino's novel Invisible Cities, a rebel in another context. Other artists who I had in mind during creation: the Japanese woodblock printing artists Kawase Hasui and Hiroshi Yoshida; American painter JAM Whistler.

Impossible cathedrals was written in p5.js using elements of code by eeedg (thanks)

metadata.name: The Color of Spring #18
metadata.description:
‚ÄúColor of Spring‚Äù : Seasons of Siskiyou Series
By Ed Cavett
March 2022

Description of Seasons of Siskiyou Series
Surrounding my home, covering more than one million acres, is the Rogue River - Siskiyou National Forest which takes up three southern Oregon counties and one northern California county.  It‚Äôs a magical place that fills the imagination and lifts the spirit; a place that inspires with its uniqueness, its legends, and its larger-than-life vistas.

Each season in the Siskiyou mountains is a unique experience unto itself.  So, with an attention to the feelings this place evokes at any given time of the year, I designed four generative tokens to create an impression of the emotion‚Äìthe calming quietness; the peaceful solitude; the overwhelming contrasts and variety of forms, shapes and textures; the magic and playful mystery; the welcomingness and foreboding.  These four works feature clever and inventive creative coding techniques in a rich, graphic style to craft a stunning impression of the Seasons of Siskiyou.


Token 1 of 4 - THE COLOR OF SPRING (1990 x 1080) p5js Generative Token.

The Color of Spring captures the playfulness and joy of the season of birth; the renewal and hopefulness of a bounty that follows warmth and light.  The weight of winter and the burdens of darkness melt away with the length of the day.  The monotones of a gray-chromatic winter bristle with bursts of bright colors in an ocean of budding green.  Magic brings forth the harbingers of fruit and the fleeting, nostalgic notes of newness and surprise.  In such a place, in such a time, we are transported back to when this was the world, and all there was in it.  With a child-mind, we are suspended in that instant while we relive all the moments like it.  And, before we have time to grow tired of it, it disappears into the brilliant light of summer.       

Output and Coding Features of ‚ÄúThe Color of Spring‚Äù:

This generative token features a stand of aspen that borders a field of wildflowers in a sea of lush, green grass.  Animated pixies tend to the flowers as they wave their wands while fluttering about the field.  Fuzzy orbs of light dance around each pixie with some that glide capricious throughout the scene.

Press UP ARROW to toggle the scene on/off leaving only the pixies and glowing orbs.  Press RIGHT ARROW to toggle Pause and Play.  Press LEFT ARROW to toggle Add and Remove pixies.  The static scene has a blurry particle effect added in.  Press DOWN ARROW to save the current frame as a png image file.  The file will be downloaded to a local folder. 


Collectors can choose to pause the animation and freeze the scene on a static image.  If collectors so desire, they may remove the pixies from the scene and appreciate the simple beauty without distraction.  Capture an image as a downloadable image file by pressing the Down Arrow.

The aspens are generated using flow-field stochastic conditions for an organic structure, and with a random expression of knots as the object is formed.

The grass and flower pedals are generated using recursions that incorporate noise-stochastic conditions.

The pixies are generated with primitive geometries using a ‚Äúmarionette‚Äù style structure.  The animation is achieved through noise-stochastic conditions that rotate segments, such as the arms, legs and feet.

Each iteration varies the order and appearance of the graphic elements; the number of pixies and the number of flowers.   

Token Published April 16, 2022 on FXHASH set at 75 Editions.
Written and designed by Ed Cavett using the p5js library.
Token 1 of 4 from the series ‚ÄúThe Seasons of Siskiyou.‚Äù
